President Biden has announced that Ed Siskel will serve as White House Counsel. Siskel previously served in the White House Counsel's Office during the Obama-Biden Administration and was Deputy Counsel. In his new role, Siskel will lead a team providing legal counsel to the President on matters facing the White House and the country. He will be responsible for crafting policies, defending and advancing the President's agenda, and working towards progress for the American people. Siskel's experience in public service and his commitment to the rule of law make him a strong choice for the position. He will replace Stuart Delery in September. Siskel has previously served as Corporation Counsel for the city of Chicago and as chief legal officer for a Chicago-based investment firm. He has also worked in the Justice Department and as a federal prosecutor. Siskel is a Chicago native and a graduate of Wesleyan University and the University of Chicago Law School.